<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10621299>
    dc:description "Figs 9. A–K – Mordellistenini, Baltic amber.A–F – Baltistena brevispina sp. nov., holotype, PřFUK95: A – habitus; B – hind leg; C – eye; D – hypopygium; E – middle leg; F – fore leg. G–K – Baltistena atronigra sp. nov., holotype, PřFUK108: G – habitus; H – eye; I – hind legs; J – hypopygium; K – base of pronotal disc and scutellum. Scale bars: A – 1.0 mm; B – 0.4 mm; C, J – 0.3 mm; D, I – 0.5 mm; E, F – 0.15 mm; G – 0.8 mm; H, K – 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10621299/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10621301>
    dc:description "Figs 10. A–F – Metakatepisternum: A – Baltimorda, undescribed species A, PřfUK71. B – Palaeostena eocenica (Kubisz, 2003), PřfUK107. C – Baltistena hoffeinsorum sp. nov., holotype, PřFUK92. D – Baltistena concava sp. nov., holotype, PřFUK93. E – Baltistena brevispina sp. nov., holotype, PřFUK95. F – Baltistena atronigra sp. nov., holotype, PřFUK108. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10621301/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

